Canon Shares Rise Most in Four Weeks After Buyback Report

-- B y   K a z u y o   S a w a
-- 
2011-05-26T00:39:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/canon-shares-rise-most-in-four-weeks-after-buyback-report.html
Canon Inc. (7751) , the worldâ€™s biggest
camera maker, rose the most in four weeks in Tokyo trading after
announcing plans to buy back as much as 1.2 percent of its total
shares.  Canon gained as much as 5.5 percent, the biggest intraday
gain since April 27, and traded 5.4 percent higher at 3,835 yen
as of 9:35 a.m. on the Tokyo stock exchange. The benchmark Topix
index rose 1 percent.  The maker of PowerShot and Ixus compact cameras said the
buyback of as many as 15 million shares would take place between
May 26 and July 28. The amount is up to 50 billion yen ($610
million), according to a statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange
yesterday.  Canon owns 105 million shares, or 7.89 percent of its total
shares as of May 23, according to the report.  To contact the reporters on this story:
